SENATE RESOLUTION 347
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the Adamsville High
School Lady Cardinals girls' basketball team
upon winning the 2026 Class 2A District 13
tournament.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this legislative body should salute those student athletes
who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as true champions of
whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary group of lasses is the Adamsville High School Lady
Cardinals girls' basketball team, whose members have proven themselves to be the fiercest of
competitors and truly worthy of admiration by winning the 2026 TSSAA Class 2A District 13
tournament; and
WHEREAS, in the championship game, the Lady Cardinals easily tamed the Scotts Hill
Lady Lions by a score of 56-33 to bring home the gold; and
WHEREAS, the Lady Cardinals' superb performance would not have been possible
without the stellar leadership of Head Coach Chad Austin, who was named District Coach of the
Year, and the unfailing support of their families, their fans, and their community; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Adamsville girls' basketball team epitomize all that is
good in today's student athletes, as they have achieved a premier level of success in
competition while exhibiting the highest degree of character in all aspects of life; and
WHEREAS, the perseverance, determination, work ethic, and talent of this group of
young ladies not only made possible an outstanding season but also surely bode well for their
future success; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud the Adamsville Lady
Cardinals for their outstanding season on the hardwood; now, therefore,
SR0347
015845
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and commend the
members and coaches of the Adamsville High School Lady Cardinals girls' basketball team
upon winning the 2026 TSSAA Class 2A District 13 tournament and reaching the sectional
round and extend to them our best wishes for every continued success in all their future
endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
